[8760535]
RogueI have a question, how does the bear do for your brute? I know they often just tank until the fight ends or they get killed, maybe getting a few attacks in a normal fight. I've never had a bear in either mybrute game, only wolves. Are they worth it?

The bear is great. He's usually more useful offense-wise on lower levels. On higher levels (20+), he starts to serve as an HP tank and soaks up damage for 4 - 5 turns, which means his primary function is to stall the fight for your brute to get a few hits in before he dies. In my experience, wolves are only useful in killing off dogs; whenever they attack my brute, they get Shield + CA'd upon so they don't last for too long. I personally think bears surpass wolves (by not that huge a margin), but I never had a wolf and I play just to cut ears, so take it with a grain of salt
